    # ── SECTION: The B2C Pivot ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Narrative_B2CPivot a narr:Narrative ;

      skos:broader narr:PositioningThesis ;
      skos:prefLabel "B2C as Primary Market: Every Individual Is Their Own Team" ;
      skos:note "The most significant outcome of the March 17 call. Both Scarlet and Tony converged independently on the idea that aswritten is fundamentally more B2C than B2B. Enterprise remains as the top tier, but the primary go-to-market is individuals and small businesses. Tony's argument: AI has made every individual their own team. The people who need structure for context and memory are solopreneurs, consultants, small business owners. The volume play is B2C. This extends the March 12 SMB pivot further — SMB was already a shift from enterprise, but B2C goes beyond SMB to include individuals building companies alone." ;
      narr:theme "AI has made every individual their own team; the volume play is B2C — solopreneurs and small business owners who need structure for context and memory" .

    narr:Claim_B2CPrimaryMarket a narr:Claim ;

      skos:note "Both Scarlet and Tony independently converged on aswritten being fundamentally more B2C than B2B. Enterprise remains as the top tier but the primary go-to-market is individuals and small businesses. This extends the March 12 SMB pivot further to include individuals building companies alone." ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_B2CPivot ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      narr:supports narr:PositioningThesis .

