    # ── SECTION: Technical User Adoption Friction ────────────────────────────
    narr:Narrative_TechnicalAdoptionFriction a narr:Narrative ;

      skos:broader narr:FrictionFailure ;
      skos:prefLabel "Technical User Adoption Friction: Contamination Fear, Not Product Difficulty" ;
      skos:note "Tony shared a critical insight about why technically sophisticated users (like himself) struggle to adopt aswritten. The reason a collaborator doesn't work for Tony is he's not all in on a collaborator. People like Tony have 10 repos on the go with Claude and all this tooling — they're worried about what's going to break or cross over. The solution: start a completely new project with aswritten, don't touch existing repos. Tony also revealed a privacy concern that drove avoidance: he didn't want experimental work visible to others. The insight: technical users with existing AI workflows have high adoption friction not because the product is hard, but because they fear contamination — their existing setup breaking, or their experimental work being visible." ;
      narr:theme "Technical users resist adoption not because the product is hard but because they fear contaminating their existing AI workflows; the solution is clear onboarding guidance to start fresh" .

    narr:Claim_TechnicalUserSeparationPrinciple a narr:Claim ;

      skos:note "Tony's insight: the best thing for technical users with existing AI workflows is to have a completely new project that hasn't started any repos, and then don't let it touch anything else. Keep them separate. The more involved people are, the more they need separation from their own chaos. This is the onboarding guidance aswritten needs to provide." ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_TechnicalAdoptionFriction ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      narr:supports narr:EnablementTraining .

    narr:Claim_PrivacyConcernDrivesAvoidance a narr:Claim ;

      skos:note "Tony revealed a privacy concern that drove his avoidance of aswritten: he didn't want experimental or sensitive work visible to others in the system. This is a distinct adoption barrier from technical complexity — it's about visibility and control of what gets recorded." ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_TechnicalAdoptionFriction ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Stake ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_TechnicalAdoptionFriction .

